<p>I have the following class</p>  <pre><code>public class A {     public virtual decimal ID { get; protected set; }     public virtual string  Locality { get; set; } } </code></pre>  <p>and this is mapped to TableA. TableA has also a column LocalityID, with the LocalityDescription being in TableB. I want to map the Locality property to TableB's LocalityDescription. I tried the following, unsuccessfully:</p>  <pre><code>        Join("TableB", m =&gt;         {             m.Fetch.Join();             m.KeyColumn("LocalityID");             m.Map(t =&gt; t.Locality).Column("LocalityDescription");         }); </code></pre>  <p>what is the proper way of doing this operation?</p>